<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-05-09T09:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-05-09T09:00:00-05:00" n="727" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d727">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/10790:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Turkey</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Ankara</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-05-09T17:00:00+03:00">May 9,
                                        1941—5 p.m.</date>
                                    <lb/> [Received 5:15 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>136. For Secretary and Under Secretary. It would appear that although
                                suggestion reported my 111, April 26, was made as a result of
                                intimation from King Greek Government ultimately rejected it. It is
                                also understood that that Government took great offence on learning
                                of Turkish approach to Germans (my 117, April 30) of which it had
                                not been informed in advance.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">MacMurray</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>